nd optionally sync the Markdown view.\r\n\r\noptions:\r\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\r\n  --kind {auto,matrix,platform}\r\n                        Authority type. auto infers from the authority\r\n                        filename. (default: auto)\r\n  --authority AUTHORITY\r\n                        Authority JSON path to patch. (default: None)\r\n  --patch PATCH         Strict JSON patch payload. Omit with --validate-only\r\n                        to just validate the authority. (default: )\r\n  --validate-only       Validate the authority without applying a patch.\r\n                        (default: False)\r\n  --dry-run             Validate and summarize without writing files.\r\n                        (default: False)\r\n  --markdown MARKDOWN   Markdown mirror path. Defaults to the authority path\r\n                        with .md suffix. (default: )\r\n  --no-markdown         Do not sync the Markdown mirror. (default: False)\r\n  --summary-json SUMMARY_JSON\r\n                        Optional path for a machine-readable patch summary.\r\n                        (default: )\r\n  --max-markdown-files MAX_MARKDOWN_FILES\r\n                        Maximum rows rendered in the Markdown mirror.\r\n                        (default: 250)\r\n  --target-project TARGET_PROJECT\r\n                        Optional target project root. When set,\r\n                        targetEndpoints touched by this patch must point to\r\n                        existing target files, with optional ::symbol checks.\r\n                        (default: )\r\n  --plan-json PLAN_JSON\r\n                        Optional strict plan.json. When set, plannedPhase\r\n                        values touched by this patch must exist in phases[].\r\n                        (default: )\r\n  --allow-missing-endpoints\r\n                        Skip targetEndpoints filesystem/symbol validation even\r\n                        when --target-project is set. (default: False)\